"2018-08-10T14:31:27Z", "closed_at": "2018-08-10T14:31:27Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "the NLL type-check currently does two walks over the MIR. One is a \"sanitize pass\"\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/a77dfcc79fe3e7e1a10ae4dccfd4b2e5e0e49195/src/librustc_mir/borrow_check/nll/type_check/mod.rs#L206-L210\r\n\r\nand then, only if sanitize pass succeeds, another walk to do \"checking\":\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/a77dfcc79fe3e7e1a10ae4dccfd4b2e5e0e49195/src/librustc_mir/borrow_check/nll/type_check/mod.rs#L212-L215\r\n\r\nIt *might* be faster to do just one? The reason, IIRC, was that we had ICEs due to weird conditions in sanitizing causing assertion failures in type-checking. It seems like we could detect and correct those.\r\n\r\nThis is based on the fact that in the profiles, I see a fair amount of time in methods like `visit_mir` that doesn't seem to be spent in other operations. But I may need to add some `#[inline(never)]` calls, perhaps I am being misled.\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "nikomatsakis", "id": 155238, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1NTIzOA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/155238?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis", "html_url": "https://github.com/nikomatsakis", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikom